results.title: Nothing Gained
results.description: Miguel fights Venture after he kills a Thorite, then leads him on a merry chase, but is captured.  He breaks free and finally defeats Venture.  In the meantime, Gabriel figures out that Spider-Man is his brother.

results.title: This is not a clone of Spider-Man 2099
Bugaboo
results.description: Spidey fights Flipside, basically a mechanical clone of himself, and finally knocks it out long enough to escape.  He returns to Nightshade and finds out about Angela's death.  He decides he still needs to wander some more.

results.title: Splitting
results.description: Xina and Angela try to talk Miguel into testifying against Kron, but apparently fail.

results.title: Route 666
results.description: Miguel is mugged while wandering in the desert, and given a dose of toxin that makes him hallucinate.  He dreams he is escorting a group of dead people, as Spidey.  He wakes up to find that Xina came after him.

results.title: Day of the Dead
results.description: Miguel and Xina go to Mexico, and run into Gabe and Kasey.  Miguel is flashblinded by a weird light, and gets away from the others to investigate.  He runs into Strange, and they team up to find out what is happening.

results.title: Hitting the Road
results.description: Miguel runs away, but a kind cab driver named Dash convinces him to return and testify against Kron.

results.title: Strange Whine
results.description: Strange and Spidey confront Morgez, the person who has caused the dead to rise.  When Strange touches the amulet he used, it brings out her dark side.  They fight, and she reverts to normal.  They trick Morgez, and destroy the amulet.

results.title: J'accuse
results.description: Miguel tricks Kron into admitting he tried to drown Miguel in the pool.

results.title: Mr O'Hara Goes to Washington
results.description: Miguel learns that Doom has taken over the country while he was out.  Tyler wants him to take over Alchemax's R&D division, and Doom wants him on his cabinet.  Oh, and his mom just shot Tyler Stone...

results.title: Bullies
results.description: Tyler tells Angela that Kron has to stay, but Angela refuses, and calls up Herod, Tyler's father-in-law, to enforce her decision.

results.title: Blood from a Stone
results.description: Miguel considers the offers, and learns that Stone has been shot.  Venom appears and tries to kill Stone, only to be distracted by Spider-Man.

results.title: Venom
results.description: Miguel takes the Alchemax job, intending to offer it to Xina.  His mom apparently commits suicide, and Gabe is going nuts over being dumped by Kasey.  Venom shows up to the party, of course, and makes Miguel choose between Dana and Xina.

results.title: It Tickled When We Kissed
results.description: Miguel remembers meeting Dana, and breaking up with Xina, as he chases Venom who is holding them both hostage.  His mom decides not to kill herself.  Xina escapes Venom temporarily, and troopers shot at Venom.  The bullets go through him and kill Dana.

results.title: Silent Scream
results.description: Miguel figures out that high frequency sound will cause venom to lose cohesion.  He has the public eye broadcast it, and Spider-Man takes out Venom.  And finds a human host inside.  The Vulture is back, but somebody is protecting Kasey from him.

results.title: Hasta La Vista
results.description: Tyler tells Kron to pack, and has a heart-to-heart with Miguel.

results.title: Brother's Keeper
results.description: Venom's human host was Kron, Miguel's old nemesis from school.  Miguel beats him up to get him to tell his story.  Father Jennifer comes to Miguel for answers about Dana's, her sister's, death.  Green Goblin is working with Vulture.

results.title: Insolent One! You Cannot Escape The Specialist!
The Specialist
results.description: Gabriel's girlfriend, Kasey, is kidnapped by Alchemax so they can run experiments on her.  When she escapes, The Specialist goes after her, and Miguel goes after The Specialist.

results.title: Judas Goat
results.description: The Goblin ambushes Spider-Man on his way to downtown.  The Goblin then reveals all the recent political actions of Spider-Man and accuses him of being a corporate stooge.  The Downtowners chase Spider-Man away.

results.title: Despair
results.description: After Dana's funeral, Miguel takes over Alchemax in the hopes that he can help make a better world with that sort of power.

results.title: Earth
results.description: Miguel is having trouble running Alchemax, he needs a good secretary.  And one arrives, just in time to help him with a mob of downtowners who want to see him.  The secretary?  His mom.

results.title: Water
results.description: Miguel goes, as Spider-Man, to rescue a mission sent to New Atlantis.  He discovers that the new race of undersea dwellers want independence, and are willing to teach the surface world a lesson to get it.

results.title: The City Shall Drown in Blood!
You've Made Fools of the Public Eye for the Last Time, Wall-Crawler!
Blood Oath
results.description: Miguel fights The Specialist, and Kasey tries to save him.  After saving The Specialist from falling to his death, Miguel accidently kills him.  The Public Eye then shoots him, and he falls Downtown.

results.title: Downtown
results.description: Miguel is badly hurt and Downtown, the bad part of the city.  He makes it to a medical center, where a follower of Thor patches him back together.  The Public Eye finds him, however, and only the timely appearance of The Vulture saves him.

results.title: A Fearsome New Foe Fights Spider-Man 2099, Vulture 2099
Wing and a Prayer
results.description: Miguel learns that Vulture is a cannibal, and tries to escape.  Gabriel goes downtown to search for Miguel, and accidently shoots Kasey.

results.title: Flight of Fancy
results.description: The battle enters a downtown cathedral, and to leave it Spider-Man faces The Vulture's cannibalistic horde, the Freakers.  Gabriel, Kasey, and friends arrive in time to help him escape, but he draws off the Vulture to fight him alone, and kills him.

results.title: Home Again, Home Again
results.description: Miguel gets back uptown and disguises himself as a Public Eye to get safely home.  Instead, he finds himself in a group of Public Eyes trying to take out a bunch of people dressed as Spider-Man.

results.title: Rocks and Waves
results.description: Kane is stranded in Cable's future and learns all he can about the mysterious Askani leader; Cable returns and informs the Clan Chosen that they must destroy a time displacement machine located in Niagra Falls; Kane has hopes that the machine can send him home before it is destroyed.

results.title: The Killing Field Part II: Like Lambs to the Slaughter
results.description: Cable joins up with the Acolytes to take down Omega Red, but the hunt takes them to Magneto's old base where the remainder of the Acolytes are waiting.

results.description: Cable has to contend with the likes of Omega Red and the Acolytes at the same time; Katu sacrifices himself to save the world from Omega Red's death spore.

results.description: Cable rescues Lee from the coils of Senyaka.

Fear & Loathing Part 3

results.title: Shadows
results.description: Cable and Domino go out on a date but Thornn interrupts.

results.title: The Phalanx Sanction
results.description: Lang diverts hodge so that Cable, Wolvie and Mr. and Mrs. Summers can infiltrate the Phalanx citadel and bring the techno organic aliens down; Which they do; Off in space, another Phalanx registers the defeat on earth and begins to make plans.

results.title: The Dark Ride Part 1: The Calling
results.description: Cable and his companions save Caliban from the Dark Riders.

results.title: The Dark Ride Part 2: Judgement Day
results.description: Cable and company chase the Dark Riders back to their leader who just happens to be Cable's son.

results.title: The Dark Ride Part 3: In the Name of the Father
results.description: Cable takes on his son; The Dark Riders are defeated; Apocalypse is awakened.

results.title: Mired in Destiny
results.description: Cable and the Clan Chosen attack the time displacement center; Cable decides to return to the present with Kane when he realizes that the bad guys have already sent someone back to the past.
